description:
&lt;p&gt;An excellent opportunity for experienced IT professionals providing IT services to 11000+ users across Warwickshire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking Systems Support Analysts to work as part of the Infrastructure Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will involve the deployment and continued support of back-end ICT hardware and software at a Tier 3 level.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidates will be able to demonstrate an excellent understanding and in-depth experience of all current Microsoft Windows Server and Desktop operating systems. Also, excellent knowledge and experience with ICT hardware.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role would be suitable for someone who has been working as an advanced Tier 2 engineer and can apply everything they know and take it to the next level. Attitude and aptitude are incredibly important as the candidate must want to progress in their ICT career, having a ‘can-do’ attitude and willing to go the extra mile for our service users.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The normal working hours are 37½ hours per week however there will be occasions on which additional cover is required during times of peak activity. Working hours are flexible between 08:00 and 18:00 according to the needs of the service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A pro-active attitude and the ability to work unsupervised whilst meeting deadlines is essential. Excellent interpersonal skills are required as there will be a significant amount of liaison with colleagues and system users throughout the Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews will be held via MS Teams week commencing 16th November&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ravi Heer – Technical Services Manager – ravi.heer@swft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Eric MacFarlane – Technical Services Manager – eric.macfarlane@swft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mike Bidwell – Technical Services Manager – Michael.bidwell@swft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Avinder Channa - Technical Service Manager - Avinder.channa@swft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
